values:
Bandwagons aren't really my bag.  I try and avoid the crowd as much as possible and do my own thing.  But I write things down enough that I guess it was only a matter of time before I gave in and did this.  I've heard about it here and there and figured what the hell, right?  Besides it's a good way to keep up with the latest town happenings and read about all the dirt in this town.  And so here I am.  

I'm not going to be like everyone else in the world and say I just suck at introductions, you can decide that for yourself.

<lj-cut text="frustrations"> 

Name: Isabelle

Age: 19

Born in: Eden, and I'm still here wondering when the fuck I'm going to get out.  

Resides in: Technically with the parents in Wellesley, but I'd be surprised if you found me there

Marital status: Single.

Care to describe your sexuality for us?: Whatever

Occupation: I'm a student.  Occasionally I'll find an odd job for some extra cash

Hobbies: Once again: whatever.  Cause hobbies mean you commit and who the fuck needs commitment? 

Turn ons: Impulsiveness, Rebels

Turn offs: Overzealousness, Self-righteousness, Megalomaniacs   

What do you hope to get out of keeping this journal: I don't plan on getting anything out of it.  it's just here

If you had to pick a theme song for yourself, what would it be?: Bif Naked - Any Day Now

Any vices or addictions?: Cigarettes, alcohol, and other things   

Complete this sentence: If people are looking for me, they can usually find me... wherever the wind takes me or something.  

Parting comments: Hopefully this will not be parting at all but just a little down time in our continued communication.
